<br>
Why would a company without ANY previous MMORPG experience manage to create a superior game which lacks all of the flaws seen in almost every MMORPG's first two years? It has always been so that a company ignores people like Jessica Mulligan (googling on her gets you some useful responses) who always try to stop them from trying to reinvent the fifth wheel.<br>
<br>
What could possibly lead you to believe that they will do an inherently superior job than anyone has done so far? Blizzard has never dealt with the scale involved, and once the game opens to the public, there WILL be people of the like found over at IGE (What's that stand for again? Independent Game Exploiters?) who will start to colonize the world. Maybe some of them already have in the beta stages.<br>
<br>
There will be major assholes and admirable saints among the playerbase, just like in any segment of the populace, and there will be bugs and PR blowouts, just like with any piece of software. What I don't understand is why the grass is so much greener over the hills. The only real distinguishing benefit to this game is being in a world with the characters of Warcraft, as far as I can see.<br>
<br>
I'm a die-hard EQ player, and with reason. Someone who would truly make a better game (not different, I seriously mean _better_) would get my money though.<br>
<br>
