<br>
The game, the engine, the control, the fun factor everything about this game is lackluster.<br>
<br>
Blizzard pours their hearts into their games and will not release garbage like SoE will. They do wait until their games are satisfactory for themselves. They have one of the best track records around for games.. I mean come on, if Diablo 2. is your worst game to date.. I think your pretty much better than any other developer out there.<br>
<br>
WoW also has alot of Old school Gamers, and MMORPG devs. They have seen and know what is good and what is bad in a game. 1 look at the official website brings so much more promise than eq ever offered. The tradeskills, the battlesystem, the quest system, the emersion, and the feel of the game looks THAT MUCH BETTER than eq.<br>
<br>
The only possible thing that worries my about Blizz is the fact that they have no mmorpg netcode experience.  Being able to support the amount of users and bandwidth that is required is the hardest thing about an mmorpg.<br>
<br>
Also you  have to remember, it was B McQuaid, and Verant who thought up EQ, and ran it for the first 2 years. The time when I feel EQ was at its peak. Once SoE gained control of it it has slowly gone down hill. <br>
<br>
I dont see anything new coming to EQ. All of the new gimmicks they have added have all been because of competition by other games. Blizzard isnt a company you can just sit around and wait to see what they do and try to imitate it.. you will get left in the dust.<br>
<br>
They have all of the major things that are needed by a MMORPG to set it up as one of the best. EVERY OTHER mmorpg to date has not all of these.<br>
<br>
A dedicated fanbase of millions of gamers that LOVE their games.<br>
Some of the best coders, and designers around.<br>
Lots of money.<br>
A drive to make the best possible game.<br>
<br>
<br>
The game isnt even in alpha yet.. but from what little everyone who has seen has saw... EQ is a fossil.<br>
