<br>
As far as WoW being a new player in the mmorpg field, that makes them better.  They've seen the mistakes of other online games - they play them too. I would say that Blizzard defines genres with it's game.  Warcraft was not the first overhead RTS, but it sure as hell made the genre popular.  <br>
<br>
And if anybody wants to make fun of Diablo, take a look at Everquest.  Meaningless hack and slash to gain points so you can kill a boss, reload the level, kill a boss, reload the level, kill them again.<br>
<br>
